description:
This is a 16 minute workout called '15 min Abs and Hip Workout | Pilates for Beginners' from the channel Flow with Mira.
The workout falls under Flexibility/Pilates and Cardio/Mat.
It's suitable for Beginner fitness levels.
The workout has a The Foundation Builder and The Reboot Workout vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: In this 15-minute gentle Pilates routine, we will guide you through a series of exercises that focus on strengthening and toning your abs and hips, perfect for anyone wanting a slower and more gentle Pilates workout. These low-impact exercises can also help relieve back pain. Combine it with another workout or use it as a standalone workout. Roll out your mat and let's get started.
